# Documentation Update Rule

After completing any feature, fix, refactor, or architectural adjustment, always update the relevant documentation before committing. This is not optional — documentation is part of the definition of done.

## When to Update

Update documentation whenever you:

- Add, modify, or remove a service, module, utility, or route
- Change how logging, tracing, encryption, or other cross-cutting concerns work
- Add or change database tables, indexes, or queries
- Add, remove, or significantly change tests (new suite, coverage change, new helpers)
- Make an architectural decision that future developers need to understand
- Change `.env` variables, Redis keys, PM2 service names, or log file paths

## Which Files to Update

| Change type | Files to update |
|---|---|
| New utility / shared module | `product/technical/services.md` (add entry under Shared Service Modules), `PROJECT_MAP.md` [TECH_STACK] if it introduces a new library |
| Changed PM2 service behaviour | `product/technical/services.md` (update service entry), `product/technical/architecture.md` if the architecture changes |
| New or changed architectural pattern | `product/technical/architecture.md`, `product/decisions/000N-<title>.md` (new ADR using the template) |
| New test suite or coverage change | `TEST_MAP.md` (Suite Index + total count), `PROJECT_MAP.md` [TESTING] total count row |
| Any of the above | `product/README.md` — update `Last updated` line |
| Change to DB schema | `product/technical/database/schema.md` |
| Change to Redis keys | `PROJECT_MAP.md` [ARCHITECTURE] Redis Key Space table |
| New ADR | `product/README.md` Decisions table, `PROJECT_MAP.md` if it affects tech stack |

## How to Update

### `PROJECT_MAP.md`
The living external-memory map. Update the relevant section in-place:
- `[TECH_STACK]` — new or changed library/tool rows
- `[ARCHITECTURE]` — service topology, Redis key space
- `[TESTING]` — suite index, total count, coverage table
- `[ORPHANS & PENDING]` — mark resolved items with strikethrough; add new open items

### `product/technical/architecture.md`
Update the affected section (Logging, Security, State Management, Transfer Pipeline, etc.). Update the `Last updated` date at the top.

### `product/technical/services.md`
Update the relevant service entry or Shared Service Modules section. Update the `Last updated` date at the top.

### `TEST_MAP.md`
Add a numbered Suite entry following the existing pattern. Update the total count table and last verified run block.

### Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)
When a non-trivial technical decision is made (choice of library, pattern, or approach with real alternatives), create a new ADR:

1. Copy `product/decisions/template.md` to `product/decisions/000N-<kebab-title>.md`
2. Fill in Status (Accepted), Date, Context, Options Considered, Decision, Consequences, References
3. Add the ADR row to `product/README.md` Decisions table
4. Reference the ADR from the relevant `PROJECT_MAP.md` or `architecture.md` section

### `product/README.md`
Update the `Last updated` line to reflect today's date and a short summary of what changed.

## Quick Checklist

Before every commit that involves code changes, verify:

- [ ] `PROJECT_MAP.md` — tech stack / testing counts / Redis keys updated if affected
- [ ] `product/technical/architecture.md` — architecture section updated if affected
- [ ] `product/technical/services.md` — service or module entry updated if affected
- [ ] `TEST_MAP.md` — suite index + totals updated if tests were added/changed
- [ ] `product/README.md` — `Last updated` line reflects today's date
- [ ] New ADR created if a significant technical decision was made
